3:
Why are we regarded as beasts;
\q why have we become stupid in your sight?
\q

5:
Indeed, the light of the wicked person will be put out;
\q the spark of his fire will not shine.
\q

7:
The steps of his strength will be made short;
\q his own plans will cast him down.
\q

9:
A trap will take him by the heel;
\q a snare will lay hold on him.
\q

10:
A noose is hidden for him on the ground;
\q and a trap for him in the way.
\q

16:
His roots will be dried up beneath;
\q above will his branch be cut off.
\q
